#!/usr/bin/env python3
# Step 15b (Kant onset validation): Kant 2017 Central Aare granite spalling
# onset under a flame-jet convective Robin BC, confining pressure p = 0.
#
# This is primarily a VERIFICATION test: does the ALAMO FEM (convective
# Robin BC + thermoelastic solve + the -sigma_xx K_I integrator + K_Ic
# table) reproduce Kant's closed-form onset calculation? Kant's experimental
# spalling temperature (553-694 C) is biased high -- his pyrometer cannot
# catch the first, smallest spall -- so it is a context anchor only, never a
# pass gate (reference packet section 6.2).
#
# Kant Eq. 15 (onset-temperature closed form, p = 0):
#   Theta_onset = K_Ic*(1-nu) / (2 * 1.763 * sqrt(a/pi) * E * alpha)
# is h_fl-INDEPENDENT and lambda-INDEPENDENT: onset dT is a material
# threshold; h_fl sets only the onset time. The setup uses lateral roller
# BCs + full-face heating so eps_xx = eps_yy = 0 is enforced exactly
# (Kant's 1-D half-space confinement) and sigma_xx = -E*alpha*dT/(1-nu) per
# cell, up to an O(dz/thermal-layer) FEM discretization residual.
#
# Targets (reference packet section 6):
#  1. VERIFICATION run (frozen room-T K_Ic0 = 1.5 -- Kant's actual Table-2
#     input): FEM onset dT in Kant's predicted band 390-560 C.
#  3. Closed-form cross-check: FEM onset dT reproduces Kant Eq. 15 (computed
#     with the SAME K_Ic treatment as the run) within TOL.
#       - verification: vs Eq. 15 with frozen K_Ic0 = 1.5
#       - model:        vs Eq. 15 with the K_Ic(T) Nasseri x1.05 table.
#         The model run's onset dT (~350-380 C) is the production model's
#         honest prediction -- reported, NOT scored against Kant's band
#         (Kant used frozen room-T K_Ic; the K_Ic(T) substitute is the
#         revised-model treatment, reference packet section 5).
#  4. a-sensitivity: halving a raises Eq. 15 onset dT by sqrt(2) (frozen
#     K_Ic; Eq. 15 scales as a^-1/2). Closed-form assertion.
#  5. h_fl-independence: input_verification (h_fl=150) and
#     input_verification_hfl (h_fl=250) give the same onset dT within TOL
#     (h_fl shifts only the onset time).
#  6. Weibull patchiness: with the per-cell flaw distribution active, first
#     firing is grain-scale patchy -- >= 5 distinct firing locations,
#     spatially spread, not the uniform sheet the homogeneous runs produce.

